Name: I'm still with it
Description: A warm-up round to kick off season 12: just submit a song released in 2023. You're still cool... right?

Name: A legit spooky playlist
Description:
Let's make a legit spooky playlist. Not the kind you've heard a million times before. Let's put our combined year of music league experience to good use. Stick to the spirit ðŸ‘»

Here are the rules:
- No novelty songs (no Monster Mash)
- No songs written for horror soundtracks (no Shining theme)
- No spooky-by-association songs â€“ Songs that arenâ€™t scary but are used in a scary movie so have become 'spooky' (i.e. Tiny Tim)
- No obvious songs (No Danzig-related, no songs called Halloween)

Name: A song you've never heard before
Description:
Honor system!

Submit a song you've never heard before and tell us in the comments how you picked. Maybe a band you've heard of but never listened to? Or heard one song but that's it? Or totally at random?

Here's the catch: it still has to be a banger. Only bangers get votes.

Name: Worst song with one redeeming quality that makes it good
Why donâ€™t people talk about this band more? Because I think theyâ€™re legendary
Description:
You have voted. You all want a nice playlist full of good songs. So submit a band you think is legendary but overlooked that we'll all like.

And no bullshit like "my chem doesn't get enough credit", "the Beatles are STILL underrated" or something. 

And Sam's rule: no obvious choices.

Name: Songs that could feature a skeleton that plays itself like a xylophone
Description:
You asked for it: spooky round 2.

This round presumes that a skeleton playing itself as a xylophone is a mostly playful act (still spooky, however) and not some horrific form of skeleton self-flagellation.

Nick Cave is banned. Monster Mash is banned. Pop punk isn't banned but you saw how it did last round so maybe learn from it.

Name: Mind Games
Description: Submit whatever you can and comment whatever you can to earn the most points. Lying, falsehoods, tricks, games, etc, whatever works to illicit points, anything goes. Whoever is the most clever will think their way into winning the round.

Name: Anti-party songs
Description: Songs about staying in, or doing uncool hobbies, or generally just keeping it low-key

Name: Old-ass songs
Description: Song must be written before 1960 (or earlier?) - but more modern cover versions of it are allowed

Name: You probably haven't heard of them
Description:
Time for some new-ass songs. Choose a great song that you think we won't have heard.

voting rule - if you've heard the band before then you can't give it any votes. If you've only heard OF the band... you can vote.
